XDUMP
  Export raw game data tables in structured text format.

SYNTAX
  xdump <table> [<uid-range>]

DESCRIPTION
  Dumps internal game data tables for use by external tools.
  Unlike 'dump', xdump can export any table and is designed for
  importing/exporting full world state.

  Common tables:
    sect    - all sectors
    nat     - nations
    ship    - ships
    land    - land units
    plane   - planes
    version - server version and configuration constants

  Output is column-separated with a header row naming each field.
  Deities can dump all countries' data.  Players see only their own.

  The companion command 'xundump' reads this format back in.

EXAMPLE
  xdump sect                dump all sector data
  xdump nat                 dump all nation data
  xdump ship                dump all ship data
  xdump version             dump server configuration

SEE ALSO
